               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16900717-2-defend31" type="defendantName">
                     Margaret 
                     Griffeth
                  <interp inst="t16900717-2-defend31" type="surname" value="Griffeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900717-2-defend31" type="given" value="Margaret"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900717-2-defend31" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was Indicted for <rs id="t16900717-2-off7" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16900717-2-off7" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16900717-2-off7" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>
               Robbing 
                     <persName id="t16900717-2-victim32" type="victimName">
                        Anthony 
                        Chewin
                     <interp inst="t16900717-2-victim32" type="surname" value="Chewin"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16900717-2-victim32" type="given" value="Anthony"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16900717-2-victim32" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900717-2-off7 t16900717-2-victim32"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , on the <rs id="t16900717-2-cd8" type="crimeDate">21st Day of June</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16900717-2-off7 t16900717-2-cd8"></join> last, of one pair of Silk Stays value 40 s. two Petty Coats 6 l. a Shirt 4 s. one lac'd Smock 10 s. &amp;c.
            </rs> It happened, that when the Fire was in Red-Lion street, not long ago, the Prosecutor lost the Goods aforesaid, but only a Bible was found upon the Prisoner, which was not in the Indictment, but she was seen to carry several things out of the House. The Prisoner denyed it, and said, that she had the Bible and a Trunk of a Man, thus gave it her in the midst of the Acclamation of Fire, and she called several Evidence who gave a Credible Account of her former behaviour, so upon the whole she was <rs id="t16900717-2-verdict9" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16900717-2-verdict9" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
